use an environment varable to customize

bash,ksh and sh use $PS1

Csh,tcsh and zsh use $prompt


\d date in weekday

\h hostname up to first period

\H hostname\n newline
\t current time 24hrs
\T current time in 12h

\@ am pm
\A
\u
\w
\W
\$ 


echo $PS1

eg: PS1="<\t \u@\h \w>\$"
"\d \t \h \W>\$"

***********
if you want to persist changes:

vi .bash_profile

